result.name: Ambrosia Oyster Bar & Grill

reviews.text: I don't eat oysters so can't share any feedback on it personally but everyone else enjoyed the large juicy and sweet ones from Ireland. Caviar from Russia was excellent and the pan fried cheese was not bad but tasted like pizza mozzarella cheese. Risotto with Boston lobster was pretty good. Overall a decent dining experience with a great view of the Hong Kong skyline.
Nice view and nice food with some live piano

The service and food standard here was excellent. Also a great place for a good view view across the bay the the skyline of Hong Kong Island. I ordered a number of different oysters and they were all fresh.
Breath-taking view.  Nice place to enjoy the laser show at night.  Good value 👍

Service was really good. Food was decent, overall a really good experience. The location was definitely a highlight and a reason to go.  Would recommend the lunch with wine, as I think it's worth the price if you have a couple of glasses with your food.

reviews.text: I don't eat oysters so can't share any feedback on it personally but everyone else enjoyed the large juicy and sweet ones from Ireland. Caviar from Russia was excellent and the pan fried cheese was not bad but tasted like pizza mozzarella cheese. Risotto with Boston lobster was pretty good. Overall a decent dining experience with a great view of the Hong Kong skyline.

Ambrosia位落於iSquare 28樓的景緻開陽，人不算太多，情侶的話建議可於book位時安排餐廳梳化位Window Seat，一邊攬著情人用餐，二人一邊看維港海景，簡直是賞心悅目。餐廳內還有鋼琴師鋼琴伴奏，氣氛浪漫得很☺️☺️ Set Dinner $598 
頭盤是暖美國帶子伴芒果莎莎及希靈魚子，芒果粒酸酸的更加突出了帶子的鮮味。

主菜點了Medium炭燒美國西冷牛扒，脂肪比例剛剛好，肉質挺鮮嫩，由於不是叫頂級的牛扒，這個價錢的牛扒也算是不錯。

炭燒澳洲羊柳 $298
這是我們另外叫的，個人喜歡羊比較羶，羊柳嫩而不膩，Ambrosia的羊柳就正合我意。
食物好。景觀一流，特別是前臨面對中環夜景。
高處俯覽維港及港島北中部景色(部分被半島酒店遮掩)是賣點。食物(半自助餐)就非常差勁。石蠔充滿鹹水，炸魚薯條用廉價魚塊。不能會第二次幫襯。
全落地玻璃景觀，環境優靜，無敵夜景。

result.name: iSQUARE

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
